programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: The Family Visit & You Get What You Put In
programme.desc: Little Briar misbehaves at kindergarten and refuses to apologize to the other kids. Ms. Olivia happens to go to the kids’ home for family visits. Briar is afraid that mom will learn about his behavior at kindergarten, so he tries various means to stop the family visit. Despite of this, Ms. Olivia still meets Briar’s mom. Seeing he could do nothing to stop the family visit, Briar tells the truth. Ms. Olivia tells Briar that he needs to confront his problems, and Briar learns a valuable lesson.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Weatherman & Herby’s Helpful Apples
programme.desc: Old Billy forecasts the weather right, and Tiki asks Old Billy to teach him how to forecast a rainy day. Tiki makes notes and memorizes it. The other kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten plan to have a picnic, and Tiki tells them the weather will be sunny. However, just when the kids are going to have the picnic, it rains. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Kitty the Tiger & The Magic Words
programme.desc: An uninvited guest, Kitty the tiger, sneaks into the drawing class, and shocks the whole class. But later this adorable tiger wins everybody’s heart. They like her, and volunteer to look after her. Kitty makes much trouble. However to make her happy, Prince Tiki lets her have his favorite bag. During naptime, kitty misses her mom so much that she can’t stop crying. Then the kids sing for her to help her sleep. It’s time to say goodbye. Everybody feels sad to part with her. Ms. Olivia promises that Kitty will attend the kindergarten when she grows up, making them happy again.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Herbert on Ice & Warmth in Cold Winter
programme.desc: The forest is covered in snow in winter. Herbert always falls down on the slippery icy road. Vick takes him to learn skating from Coach Mack. However, Herbert is afraid he will fall down and doesn’t want to try. Luna-Loo let him sit on a chair. Herbert thinks it really fun to slide on ice. He tries to learn skating and finds out it’s not as hard as he has imagined. As he skates better and better, he finally understands things are not that difficult once he tries.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Shadow has an extraordinary taste of tea and who at the same time an excellent brewer. She trains Hoffen to make him acquire the sixth sense. Hoffen spends a lot time watching Shadow brew wine since he finds it’s a little bit beyond him to acquire the subtle sixth sense. The other day Hoffen is lured into the Devoid Bamboo Bush by the two weasels. Star Kid here is completely lost there. He tries every possible direction but still can’t get out of the bush. Hoffen feels desperate when he hears his master’s sound, following which Hoffen finally acquire the sixth sense and walks out the mysterious bush.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Hoffen and Rascal, under the instruction of Shadow, come all the way to Mount Crouch to locate his last master among the Circle of Twelve, Epsilon the dragon. They are not able to find the spirit of Epsilon rather than his real physical body. The dragon’s spirit is now called Traceless, who challenges Star Child in order to know thoroughly his kung fu skills. Hoffen convinces this mysterious master with a victory. Traceless tells Hoffen that he is trapped by Nian with a lock named Keyless. Hoffen is now determined to smash the lock to free Traceless.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Hoffen is about to destroy the lock when the Enforcer appears. The crow tries to stop Hoffen but in vain. Hoffen is surprised to see the strange lock Keyless absorb his inner energy each time he hits it. Hoffen calms himself down before he finally finds the weakness of the lock. Star Kid smashes the lock and free Traceless from it. Traceless takes Hoffen to the hideout of Nian, where they can also expect Rascal, who let the weasels lead the way for him.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: A Whole New World & Bramble the Brave
programme.desc: Little Briar takes Vick’s axe and runs away with little Bramble. Vick follows them to the Pine Tree Kindergarten and meets many little animals there. Ms. Olivia tells him not to be afraid, and soon Vick gets along with the little animals there. Little Briar doesn’t want to join Vick and the other animals, seeming a bit lonely. Ms. Olivia then encourages little Briar to play with the others. At last, the kids at the kindergarten have a good time listening to Vick telling stories of the outside world.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Light Up, Little Guy & Happy Camping
programme.desc: The kids get in a cave of fireflies by chance, where they meet a firefly that can’t glow. They try to help it, but none of the methods work. Coach Mack tells them that a firefly takes in oxygen through air holes on its belly, and the more it takes in, the brighter the light it generates. By utilizing this principle, they encourage the little guy to light up at last.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: A Bear’s Gotta Do What A Bear’s Gotta Do & The Watermelon Patch
programme.desc: Young Little Bramble is dependent on his brother doing everything, otherwise he’s gonna cry. Little Briar loves his little brother so he always makes a compromise. He takes him to school, lets him have the bigger apple, and win the game. In math class, Little Bramble is required to answer questions by himself. He fails and bursts into tears. After school, Little Bramble, who’s eager to catch up with Briar, walks home alone and works out math questions all by himself. Now he understands what his brother says, a bear’s gotta do what a bear’s gotta do.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.sub-title: Be Our Guest & Grow Bramble Grow!
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble invite Hoo Hoo to their lair. In order to treat their guest the best they can, they offer Hoo Hoo the best things they have, which turns out to be a great torture to Hoo Hoo instead. Hoo Hoo can’t stand it anymore and even finds herself unable to fly. Luckily, Mama Bear arrives home and saves her. She tells her sons --- Walk in others’ shoes, and then you’ll know what they really want. Then they provide Hoo Hoo with what she really needs, and have a wonderful dinner together.

programme.title: Boonie Cubs
programme.desc: Coach Mack teaches the kids not to open the door to strangers at class, and the next day, he disguises as a stranger to test the bear brothers. Mama bear cooperates with Coach Mack on the test and leaves home. Coach Mack tries various means to get the bear brothers to open the door, but to no avail. At last, the bear brothers pass the test.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: The cubs break the trophy they won at the sports meeting. Fear of being criticized by Ms. Oliva, they make up a story that a blue bird attacks Briar and accidentally breaks the trophy. Ms. Olivia sees through their lie and gives them a lesson on honesty. The cubs confess their fault, and fix the trophy together.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bramble decides to keep the caterpillar he finds on his head, and see how it grows up and becomes a butterfly. As time goes by, the caterpillar becomes a pupa, and soon it will turn into a butterfly. But in the process of metamorphosis, Bramble worries that it might get stuck, and tries to help. Ms. Olivia stops him and tells him that it needs to do it itself to get enough strength to fly. Just as they expected, the butterfly finally comes out, dries its wings, and flies.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: The kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten are discussing what they want to be when they grow up. Vick says he wants to be an inventor and boasts that it’s easy to invent. To prove his point, he wants to invent something to dig holes as well as something for him to fly. However, both inventions meet with failure. Just when he is discouraged, he sees little Briar and Tiki playing paper planes. They are having a little contest. Then Vick gets an idea when he sees Bramble’s balloon. He attaches the balloon to the paper plane, and invents a “balloon plane” which could fly the most distance.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: The cubs have got a new classmate – Ernie Jo, whose ears look different. A rumor starts that Ernie Jo’s big ears are infectious. Everybody tries to avoid him until Babu touches one of his ear by accident and he’s totally fine. The rumor is cleared and the cubs accept him. They invite Ernie Jo to play hide and seek. With the help of his big ears, Ernie Jo leads the cubs to find Little Vick who has fallen asleep and snores during the game. Now everybody wishes to have big ears like Ernie Jo’s do.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Rainy Day Fun & The More, The Better?
programme.desc: Violet hates rainy days. She doesn’t get why the others are having fun as usual. She tries to practice her flute, but rain drops cause her flute to get out of tune. Violet gets quite embarrassed and bursts into tears. To comfort her, everybody else gets busy doing funny tricks. Violet stops crying, asks why they enjoy the rain, and finds her own fun on rainy days.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Monkey See Monkey Do & Where Does Water Come From?
programme.desc: Coach Mack organizes a show about sports. Tiki plans to do the stick trick, but he finds out Violet’s ribbon dance looks elegant. So he begins to mimic Violet’s movements and the way she speaks. The others think he is acting funny. At the show, Tiki mimics Violet’s dance. It turns out strange and he accidentally trips. Coach Mack learns about the reason why he is acting like that and tells him to choose what’s suitable for him. Tiki becomes himself again and performs his stick trick successfully.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Are You Ready? & The New Football
programme.desc: The cubs are going for a field trip. Coach Mack tells them to pack some necessary items for the trip. Bramble only packs some food. During the trip, he is disappointed to find out he doesn’t bring any drawing materials or even a cup. He goes with Luna-Loo and Violet to get some water at a creek. Then it starts to rain. Bramble doesn’t bring an umbrella and gets wet. Coach Mack goes to bring him umbrella and gets him back to the tent. Bramble realizes he’s been causing trouble to others and apologizes. He understands to listen to his teacher and pack all the necessary items for a trip.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: The Helping Board & The Balloon Burst
programme.desc: Bramble worries people might get tripped by the fallen branches after the rain, so he tries to clear the branches on the road. Warren and Herbert offer to help. Bramble goes to dump the branches. Sheriff Chinchilla see Herbert and Warren, and takes a picture of them. The picture is posted on the Helper Board in the kindergarten the next day. Bramble feels sad that he isn’t in the picture. Sheriff happens to come to the kindergarten to take some pictures, so Bramble follows her around. He hopes the sheriff can take a picture of him doing some good deeds. But Bramble causes only trouble instead. He sees Violet who’s sweeping the fallen leaves, and realizes it doesn’t matter whether to get praised or not.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Where is Tiki? & The Gift of Joy
programme.desc: Vick teaches Tiki how to ride a bike. Tiki wants more practice and borrows Vick’s bike. He promises to return it before noon. However, Vick still doesn’t get his bike back when noon passes and is worried that Tiki might fall from the bike. On his way to find Tiki, Vick learns from his friends that Tiki takes Luna-Loo and Violet for a ride. Vick doesn’t feel happy about that. He finds out his bike is broken when he finally finds Tiki. The two friends have a quarrel. Luna-Loo and Violet come and explain that Tiki was just trying to help them. Tiki and Vick apologize to each other. They all help Vick fix his bike.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch the rabbit and her senior fellow apprentice Trapper are performing acrobatics on the stage. Velvet Touch does not perform actions according to plan and muffs the performance. In the end the stage is even destroyed. In the evening, Velvet Touch’s master calls her over. He says that he plans to establish a chain acrobatics troupe and asks her to serve as leader. Velvet Touch feels very happy but Trapper knows that the master just makes an excuse to turn her away. Trapper is worried about Velvet Touch and decides to stay with her. The next morning, Velvet Touch gets up and finds that all the people have gone except Trapper. She is very sad and realizes that her master has abandoned her. Trapper consoles him and promises to assist her in the future days.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Velvet Touch and Trapper stop at Carrotown for a rest. At night, Trapper transforms himself into Mad Wolf. He goes to plough twelve thousand square meters of field and digs out lots of treasures, which help villagers get over the great drought. Velvet Touch hears about Mad Wolf’s chivalric story and admires him a lot. Just then, she sees Trapper sleeping outside the house covered with mud and starts complaining about him.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: The annual dragon boat race is cancelled due to the upcoming flood but the dragon boats are still on the river. Most villagers go to reap the harvest and only a few people are trying to pull the boats onto the bank. The tea shop owner Mr. Ferret is very anxious and says that villagers will inevitably suffer great losses once the flood pours in and destroys the boats. After hearing the news, Trapper transforms himself into Mad Wolf again in the evening and begins to pull the boats ashore one by one.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Two watchmen tell the Kitchen God that Mad Wolf is well qualified to be a sacred animal, and then the Kitchen God flies to Carrotown to look for him. He comes across with many people but cannot find the right one. He walks into a teahouse and sees Trapper putting on a variety show. He talks to Trapper for a while and rules out the possibility of his being the right person he needs.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: It's all Because of the Lollipop
programme.desc: Joe Croaker finds himself a treat of a large lollipop. After gorging on it, Joe places the hollowed lollipop around his neck and starts to toy with it. Not until he tries in vain to remove the lolly does he realize that he is stuck in it. As the lolly around Joe’s neck begins to melt, it becomes sticky and attracts many leaves to it. Joe looks just like a scary monster in that leafy lollipop! The other bug buddies are all frightened at the sight of Joe, mistaking him for the ruthless monster that has swallowed Joe alive. To revenge their good friend, the folks conceive a plan to capture “the monster”. Joe is cornered into a big ditch, where the lollipop around his neck is broken apart by McBroom’s dung ball. Not until then do the folks realize that the “monster” is none other than Joe Croaker! Just when the frog is about to fly off the handle, his buddies have already made themselves scarce.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is intrigued when he sees Niddy travels with her silk. The frog believes he might be able to do the same.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Joe's got a Fish Bone in His Throat
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is on the prowl for food and the fish obtained by Cosmo makes his mouth water. As is typical of Joe Croaker the greedy bully frog, he snatches the fish from Cosmo and quickly swallows it whole. But such voracity only results in the bones being stuck in Joe’s throat. Seeing Joe in great pain, Cosmo is in panic and at a loss what to do to help. At that moment, Bartle Bee happens to pass by and offers Joe his nectar to help ease the pain. But it fails to work. Then Bartle suggests two possible solutions he learnt from books, which are ramming down the bones with a bun and dissolving them with vinegar. Cosmo and Joe hurry to the Garbage can and score both a bun and a bottle of vinegar, but it turns out neither way helps remove the bones from Joe’s throat. In the end, proposed again by the resourceful Bartle Bee, they hang Joe Croaker upside down and succeed in swinging the bones out of Joe’s throat.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Fed up living in his shabby can house, Cosmo decides to find himself a sleek, cozy new place. First he is taken with the fancy-looking paper box with pretty patterns and good light, but Bartle Bee reminds him of its vulnerability to rain in wet seasons. So he keeps on searching his dream home. Then, a crystal clear glass jar commands Cosmo’s attention. Just when he is about to make it his new abode, the mole cricket’s warning against this heat-accumulating material discourages him from settling down there. So Cosmo has to look for other alternatives. Then he discovers a large magnet which he uses to attract pieces of parts together and make them into a solidly constructed iron house. After a long day’s rushing about, Cosmo retires to rest at his pleasant new home. But something bad happens. A coin is drawn to the magnet house and blocks the exit. Trapped inside his own house, Cosmo shouts for help, which invites Joe Croaker over. The frog agrees to help him out on the condition that Cosmo offers him both service and food. But instead of getting Cosmo out, Joe accidentally sets a large iron lid running, which crashes into the magnet house. Luckily enough, Cosmo is able to survive with the help of the mole cricket. In the end, Joe Croaker has to compensate Cosmo by offering him his service instead.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo has got a nice ice cream postage stamp, which is overheard by Joe Croaker. The thought of the tasty ice cream tempts the amphibian into a plot to steal the stamp from Cosmo. He tails Cosmo, and tries in vain to grab the stamp. Tired from the flight, Cosmo rests himself upon a branch, covering himself with the stamp. Seeing this as a good opportunity, Joe employs every possible method known to him to try to score the stamp. But none of them really works. Then the green vines hanging down the tree inspire him. He uses the vines to climb up and reaches out for the stamp. He then falls off onto the ground along with the stamp. Just when Joe assumes he has secured the ice cream stamp for good, a gust of wind blows it up to the tree again. Cosmo wakes up and joyfully takes the stamp back home.

programme.title: The Smurfs

programme.sub-title: The Smurfs And The Money Tree

programme.title: The Smurfs

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The good fairy, Guinilda gives Greedy a magic porridge pot that Brainy causes to overflow into the village and forest. The good-hearted fairy hurries to the rescue and then asks for the pot back to give to an orphanage of hungry children.

programme.desc: Smurfette discovers the evil with Chlorhydris's wicked plan to cast "a world without love" spell at the magic wishing well. It's a race against time for the Smurfs and Cupid to save the day!

programme.desc: The Smurflings free the Smurfs from the clutches of Gargamel just in time to get Baby to its first word ceremony. Baby utters the word « Gargamel ». Papa Smurf says that this word indicates that Baby will one day become the Great Chief, as he is aware of the dangers in life.

programme.title: The Smurfs

programme.desc: Hogapatra, the hideous, bloated, vulgar Queen of the Nile, cannot get to sleep and this causes huge bags under her eyes. Her beauty recipe requires squeezing sleep from Lazy Smurf...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs take Grandpa Smurf to the King's castle so that he can meet Peewit. But what with one thing and another (especially another), the Smurfs and Peewit are taken aboard a Viking long ship. The Vikings take Peewit to be their mythical Great Warrior, the one who is going to vanquish the Storm King. Can the Smurfs help Peewit out of his quandary?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs don't want to be pirates stealing gold from passing galleons. But they fall under the spell of the magic Clamulet and become the crew of Bluebeak the Parrot.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurflings accompany Woolly on his mission to shear wool for winter clothes. They must overcome obstacles such as Gargamel, a wolf and finally a shepherd boy who will not accept smurfberries as payment for the wool. The Smurflings and Woolly develop respect for one another through their travels.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfs would make delicious meals for the evil wizard Gargamel if it weren't for two things: they're difficult to catch and they're so tiny. Now, suppose there were a formula to change these bite-size snacks into big, juicy square blue meals... Gargamel has an idea...

programme.title: Heart Of Gold
programme.desc: Whatever Brainy Smurf says, the Clockwork Smurf devised by Handy has feelings just like any normal blue Smurf. At least it seems to be so until Clockwork Smurf loses what Handy had fitted inside its ribcage: a heart of gold. When the evil wizard Gargamel and his apprentice Scruple find the tiny contraption and fit it with a heart of stone, the Smurfs are in for a bad time...

programme.title: The A-Maze-Ing Smurfs
programme.desc: Jokey Smurf is dying to meet Melchior the Magnificent, creator of the famous Vanishing Box trick. Can Gargamel catch the Smurfs in Melchior's Amazing Maze?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Simon is lost in the forest and in search of his parents. Simon is the son of a couple of giants. The Smurfs try to bring him home, but then Gargamel interrupts the party.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In another Smurf theatrical super-production based – very loosely – on Alexandre Dumas' characters, a masterpiece of the stage is created, with a few lines from Romeo and Juliet thrown in.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When Brainy loses his glasses, he drops things, runs into objects, and becomes just as helpless as Clumsy, who now has to read to Brainy and help him get around. This experience makes Brainy feel guilty for the way he always made fun of Clumsy. He treats him with more respect once he receives a new pair of glasses.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh, sure, kickball (or smurfball, as they call it) is all right for a while. But it gets sort of boring after a few centuries. Now there's this new game that has been invented by a nondescript Smurf, a game where you hit a ball with a stick and send it into a gopher hole...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: This is the dramatic, moving story of the friendship between Smurfette and her pet mouse. A sad event reduces Smurfette to tears... Can the Smurfs comfort the despairing Smurfette?

programme.title: Heavenly Smurfs
programme.desc: Once again, Gargamel's infallible plan to catch the Smurfs has been foiled. But the Smurfs play a trick on him: disguised as tiny blue angels, they will teach him to mend his ways...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Thinking Baby Smurf is a leprechaun, two poachers kidnap him and try to get the small one to tell them where his pot of gold is hidden. Papa Smurf organizes everyone to attack the villains with Smurfberry pies so Baby can escape.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf's worries make him break into a rash of worrywarts. The only way to relieve him of his bout of indecision-inducing disease is to have him rub the horn of a Wartmonger, a sloppy, slimy, stupid and brutal enemy of the Pussywillow Pixies...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Accidents do happen. This time it is Jokey Smurf's mistake that ends up with his shadow coming to independent life! And the shadow loves to play practical jokes on the whole population of the Village of the Smurfs...

programme.title: The Horn Of Plenty
programme.desc: Mother Nature always does her best, but this time she's gone wrong. Her wand gets the wrong results and she accidentally damages the Autumn harvest. Now the Smurfs and all the forest animals face a lean and hungry winter. The only place where the Smurfs could get food would be the Land of Plenty. But Gargamel steals the famed Horn of Plenty to lure the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Magic Earrings
programme.desc: Hogatha manages to obtain the magic golden earrings of Sonoria that will enable her to hear Smurfy voices from afar. Following Lazy's snores, she almost reaches the Smurf Village until Harmony's horn-blasts blow in her earrings and she flies home in a rage.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf organizes a crew to sail to Smurfberry Island because Gargamel has killed all of the trees except one to trap the Smurfs. Gargamel follows them, but once more fails to catch them because the Witch of Smurfberry Island sends her nose-eating seagulls after them.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurfette leads the Smurflings on a nature hike, but Puppy gets too far ahead and they chase him into the land of the Wartmongers. King Bullrush captures them in bubbles and imprisons them. A group of rebels rescue the Smurflings and they escape on the back of Puppy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Snappy and Nat steal Gargamel's formula to make another Smurf – a female to be a companion to Smurfette. They create Sassette, who causes mischief wherever she goes. Papa uses his Smurfiness Solution to turn Gargamel's evil Sassette into a playful Smurfy Sassette.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogapatra, the hideous, bloated, vulgar Queen of the Nile, cannot get to sleep and this causes huge bags under her eyes. Her beauty recipe requires squeezing sleep from Lazy Smurf...

programme.title: Secret Of The Village Well
programme.desc: Why is Clumsy Smurf waiting day and night near the Village well? What is the wish that he wants to be kept secret? How is Gargamel going to be mixed up in this mysterious affair? Is Gargamel going to catch the Smurfs at last?

programme.title: The Littlest Witch
programme.desc: On an errand to Witch Haven for Papa Smurf, the little blue creatures meet a tiny witch and teach her how to be good while at the same time cause another witch to lose her wicked powers for one year after she falls into the river.

programme.title: To Smurf A Thief
programme.desc: The Smurfs and Homnibus befriend an unfortunate boy who is forced to steal for his master. Soon, the evil thief is turned over to the magistrate and the boy is happy to live with Homnibus.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy, wanting to be popular, steals one of Gargamel's magic spells but it backfires and turns him into a dragon. It takes all of the little blue people and Papa Smurf to sneak back to the wizard's castle to find the antidote that turns Clumsy back to his normal smurfy self.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Greenpeedeepee Swamp is the only place you can find Swamp Root, the delicious and necessary ingredient of Greedy Smurf’s famed swamp root stew. Unfortunately, it is also one place where you can find those hideous Wartmongers. Even though Sassette and the Smurfs save a young Wartmonger’s life, they still end up being captured by the others. But the Scarlet Croaker will save them! Maybe.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs don't want to be pirates stealing gold from passing galleons. But they fall under the spell of the magic Clamulet and become the crew of Bluebeak the Parrot.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: Marco Smurf And The Pepper Pirates
programme.desc: The Smurfs sail off in their sailing boat to save Marco Smurf, who has been captured at sea by Captain Pepper. Marina and a dolphin help to free Marco.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs are on a paradise Pacific Island. Well, not exactly paradise, since there is a very active volcano, on which a very active Hefty Smurf risks his life as well as Smurfette's!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurf village institutes a fire brigade to battle the flames in Greedy's kitchen only to discover that Gargamel has taken all of their water. Not realizing the weakness of his dam, Gargamel and Azrael are washed away when it breaks and floods the Smurf village, extinguishing the fire.

programme.title: Cut-Up Smurfs
programme.desc: There's nothing Sassette enjoys more than cutting up paper dolls. She does it with flair and gusto. But Papa Smurf's revitalisation formula somehow gets sprinkled on Sassette's parchment creations with unforeseen results...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Handy gives Smurfette a pair of rose-colored glasses that are instrumental in luring her into Gargamel's clutches. Fortunately, a hungry giant comes visiting, tries the glasses on, which make Gargamel look very appetizing. As he chases the wizard, the Smurfette escapes.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf recalls Dreamy's exciting voyage on the high seas and his gripping adventures with sea turtles, whales, desert islands... and pirates!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Costal Magico De Santa Claus
programme.desc: Si hay algo que desagrada a la malvada hechicera Clorhidris es la bondad y el amor propios de la Navidad. Trama un plan para robar el costal magico de Santa Claus, en el que transporta todos los juguetes que los ninos que se han portado bien reciben por Navidad. Sin embargo, no sabe que un enfurrunado Pitufo Grunon esta escondido dentro del saco.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Que, o quien, es ese extrano ser que hay en el bosque? Se asemeja vagamente a un Pitufo, pero castanetea los dientes como la ardilla que parece acompanarle... ¿y por que habla Papa Pitufo acerca del Pitufito Perdido?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado brujo Gargamel pide al mago Balthazar una receta para capturar a los pitufos. Implica secuestrar a la Madre Naturaleza para impedir la llegada de la Primavera. Por suerte, los pitufos salvan la situacion.

programme.title: Cosas Que Putifan En La Noche
programme.desc: Cuando Pitufo Colerico pierde a su oso de peluche Huggy, no consigue dormir a pesar de los esfuerzos de Papa Pitufo por convencerle de que los osos de peluche son magicos y pueden cuidar de si mismos. Gargamel se tropieza con la Aldea Pitufa y Huggy regresa convertido en un oso gigante para espantar y salvar a Pitufo Colerico.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El rio Pitufo ha desaparecido: alguien lo ha congelado cerca de su nacimiento. Los Pitufos viajan hasta el pais de la Emperatriz Esmeralda para descubrir cual es el problema y se encuentran con el Oso Parches y los Piratas de Hierro.

programme.title: Campanas De Boda Para Gargamel
programme.desc: Los Pitufos se hacen amigos de una dama en apuros que esta prometida a Gargamel, ya que convencen a su padre de que el estupido mago esta loco.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada manana, los duendecillos del agua depositan rocio sobre las hojas del bosque. No imaginas todo lo que ocurrira cuando Pitufo Miedoso se transforme con la varita magica que crea las gotas de rocio...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Jamas debes comer dulces cuya procedencia desconozcas. Incluso si los dulces tienen forma de casa y estan en lo mas profundo de la Selva Negra. Los Pitufos no pueden resistirse a comer algunas partes de la casa de dulces y los problemas comienzan de inmediato.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Labrador se pregunta que hace una calabaza en el melonar, cuando deberia estar junto a los colinabos. Cuando Pitufo Labrador tira de la calabaza y la separa del suelo, libera a un genio que comienza a llamarle amo e insiste en concederle deseos. El ansia del genio, llamado Gourdy, por complacer a Pitufo Labrador hara que, mas que en una ayuda, se convierta en una molestia.

programme.title: El Mal Genio
programme.desc: Los Pitufos encuentran un Genio en una lampara que se niega a concederles sus deseos sin la palabra magica.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Bebe Pitufo ha perdido el interes por los juguetes. Ni siquiera las sorpresas de Pitufo Bromista consiguen entretener al pequeno. Abuelo Pitufo propone hacer una visita al Juguetero, el encargado de fabricar juguetes para los ninos de todo el mundo. O mas bien, el que los fabricaba: el Juguetero esta cansado del poco aprecio que demuestran por sus juguetes aquellos que los reciben.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: A pesar de que Abuelo Pitufo les advierte de que no es bueno sacar a los animales silvestres de su habitat, los Pitufitos, que regresan de un largo viaje en el globo magico, traen con ellos a Nebbit, una divertida y adorable criatura. Y, aunque es divertida y adorable por un tiempo, entonces las cosas se complican...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel cree que crear a Pitufina fue el peor error de su vida. Pero, si pudiera lograr que recuperara su malignidad original, conseguiria a todos los Pitufos de un plumazo. ¿Volvera Pitufina a comportarse de forma malvada?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Durante su estancia en Africa, los Pitufos conocen al principe Bakuri, que puede transformar cualquier cosa en oro gracias a una estatuilla magica con forma de rinoceronte. Pero un codicioso mercader roba el amuleto y a Pitufo Filosofo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos y Omnibus se hacen amigos de un desdichado joven cuyo maestro le obliga a robar. Pronto, el malvado ladron es entregado al magistrado y el joven esta encantado de irse a vivir con Omnibus.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La bruja Hogata promete a Gargamel un silbato magico si este le presenta al brujo de sus suenos. Sin embargo, ambos se enganan mutuamente con sus triquinuelas: Gargamel se disfraza de brujo, y el silbato magico de Hogata es simplemente un reclamo para aves.

programme.title: Los Pitufos Y El Arbol Del Dinero
programme.desc: El mago malvado Gargamel ha elaborado otro plan diabolico con la ayuda de su madre, quien no es mas agradable que el. El quiere persuadir a los Pitufos con dinero pero ellos no saben lo que les espera. ¿Pitufo Goloso caera en la trampa?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Fortachon tiene un monton de cualidades: masculinidad, encanto, una sonrisa cautivadora y un bonito tatuaje en el brazo. Quiza eso es lo que provoca que una orangutana gigante de la jungla se enamore de el.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Goloso Y La Olla De Estofado
programme.desc: El hada buena Guinilda entrega a Pitufo Goloso una olla magica, pero Pitufo Filosofo hace que se desborde e inunde la aldea y el bosque. La bienintencionada hada acude al rescate y pide que le devuelvan la olla para darsela a un orfanato de ninos hambrientos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufina descubre la maldad con el maligno plan de Chlorhydris de lanzar un hechizo de "mundo sin amor" al pozo magico de los deseos. ¡Es una carrera contrarreloj para que los Pitufos y Cupido puedan arreglar las cosas!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: La Primera Palabra De Bebe Pitufo
programme.desc: Los Pitufitos liberan a los Pitufos de las garras de Gargamel justo a tiempo para llevar a Bebe Pitufo a la ceremonia de su primera palabra. Bebe Pitufo pronuncia la palabra «Gargamel». Papa Pitufo afirma que esa palabra indica que Bebe Pitufo se convertira un dia en un gran lider, ya que significa que es consciente de los peligros de la vida.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo se encuentra indefenso cuando se le acaban las bayas magicas que utiliza para sus pociones. Afortunadamente, los pequenos Pitufos encuentran un bebe de dragon en el bosque y con su ayuda...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogapatra, la espantosa, hinchada y vulgar reina del Nilo, no puede dormir y eso hace que le aparezcan grandes ojeras. Su receta para la belleza incluye exprimir a Pitufo Perezoso para extraerle sueno...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Falso Y El Feo Plumaje
programme.desc: ¿Que pueden hacer los Pitufos para salvar a este futuro pollo de buitre? Ahora mismo, aun esta en el huevo y deben encontrar la forma de incubarlo. Y sucede que el malvado mago Gargamel ha encontrado una forma de transformarse en un ave para acercarse a los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Labrador se pregunta que hace una calabaza en el melonar, cuando deberia estar junto a los colinabos. Cuando Pitufo Labrador tira de la calabaza y la separa del suelo, libera a un genio que comienza a llamarle amo e insiste en concederle deseos. El ansia del genio, llamado Gourdy, por complacer a Pitufo Labrador hara que, mas que en una ayuda, se convierta en una molestia.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Abuelo Pitufo llevaba algunos cientos de anos sin ver su antiguo juguete. Se lo entregaron a Papa Pitufo hace mucho tiempo y no recuerda exactamente como funciona. ¡Pero Bebe Pitufo sabe que tiene sorpresas para todos!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Que, o quien, es ese extrano ser que hay en el bosque? Se asemeja vagamente a un Pitufo, pero castanetea los dientes como la ardilla que parece acompanarle... ¿y por que habla Papa Pitufo acerca del Pitufito Perdido?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: La Primera Palabra De Bebe Pitufo
programme.desc: Los Pitufitos liberan a los Pitufos de las garras de Gargamel justo a tiempo para llevar a Bebe Pitufo a la ceremonia de su primera palabra. Bebe Pitufo pronuncia la palabra «Gargamel». Papa Pitufo afirma que esa palabra indica que Bebe Pitufo se convertira un dia en un gran lider, ya que significa que es consciente de los peligros de la vida.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo recuerda las emocionantes aventuras de Sonador en el mar, con tortugas, ballenas, islas desiertas...y piratas!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Esta vez, Gargamel se siente seguro de si mismo. Bueno, casi... ¡Esta a punto de atrapar a los pequenos Pitufos! Las ligerisimas tortitas de Pitufo Goloso casi provocan que los Pitufos floten hasta quedar al alcance de Gargamel.

programme.title: La Aguja Magica De Pitufo Sastre
programme.desc: Pitufo Sastre tiene que crear un conjunto para cada Pitufo antes del desfile de moda de otono. Pitufo Filosofo quiere ayudarle y, usando el libro de magia de Papa Pitufo, conjura una aguja magica que cose diez veces mas rapido que un sastre... ¿Pero es eso algo realmente bueno?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Armonia ya no es bienvenido en el coro de los Pitufos: canta de una manera demasiado desafinada. Sin embargo, Papa Pitufo le entrega un amuleto que le convertira en un virtuoso del canto. Y, por si fuera poco, aqui llega Hogata...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada manana, los duendecillos del agua depositan rocio sobre las hojas del bosque. No imaginas todo lo que ocurrira cuando Pitufo Miedoso se transforme con la varita magica que crea las gotas de rocio...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un siniestro extrano aparece en la guarida de Gargamel. Es un cazador de recompensas. Por un modico precio, siempre consigue capturar a su presa. Y, si Gargamel le ofrece oro, ¡por supuesto que atrapara a los Pitufos!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En la antigua China, la fortuna se esconde en las galletas del Pitufo Goloso, y Pitufo Filosofo es el escritor. Es una oportunidad demasiado buena para hacer travesuras como para que Pitufo Bromista la desperdicie.

programme.title: Peligro En La Aldea
programme.desc: El perfido mago Gargamel esta harto de la constante superioridad de los Pitufos. Decide destruir su aldea de una vez por todas. Con ese fin, entrena una termita para que destroce, demuela, devaste y destruya todas las casas que se encuentre en su camino. Sin embargo, los efectos son mucho peores de lo que Gargamel habia imaginado, ya que los Pitufos creen que las travesuras de los Pitufitos son las que estan destruyendo su aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos serian un delicioso manjar para el malvado mago Gargamel si no fuera por dos cosas: son dificiles de atrapar y tambien muy pequenos. Ahora bien, si hubiera una formula que permitiera transformar a esos pequenos aperitivos de bocado en grandes y jugosas raciones azules... Gargamel ha tenido una idea...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Patoso y sus desventuras le llevan a traves de un rio a un lugar desconocido. Alli conoce a las duendecillas, unas adorables criaturitas cuyos enemigos acabaran encontrandose con los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el hada de las flores aparece en el pueblo de los Pitufos, todos se enamoran de su encanto e inteligencia. Y pronto se daran cuenta de que se convertira en una especie de mama pitufo para todos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Mientras intenta escabullirse de sus tareas, Pitufo Perezoso encuentra un antiguo pozo abandonado con una interesante peculiaridad: cualquier objeto que uno baje en el cubo regresa como nuevo. Pero ¿es eso bueno?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En su busqueda de algo novedoso, Pitufo Vanidoso se pone un sombrero magico creado por Gargamel que le deja la cara hecha un adefesio. Mediante una argucia, Papa Pitufo consigue robarle el antidoto al malvado mago, logrando asi que Pitufo Vanidoso recupere su belleza.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo decide celebrar una fiesta de la cosecha, y todos los Pitufos compiten en el concurso de «Mr. Pitufo» por el honor de ser el acompanante de Sasita. Gargamel se cuela en el concurso despues de encoger su cuerpo con un tinte azul magico, con la esperanza de capturar a todos los Pitufos cuando vuelva a su tamano normal. Los Pitufos le echan y Sasita decide que Papa Pitufo sera su acompanante.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel vierte una pocion similar al pegamento sobre Pitufo Torpe y, cuando alguien le toca, se queda pegado a el. Los Pitufos acaban adheridos entre si hasta que Papa Pitufo agarra a Gargamel por la nariz. Gargamel, molesto por tener a todos los Pitufos pegados a el, elabora un antidoto para la pocion y los Pitufos vuelven a ser libres.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un monstruo del pantano secuestra a Bebe Pitufo como regalo para una bruja. La bruja, que cree que nadie la ama, se sorprende cuando Bebe Pitufo le demuestra afecto. Cuando Papa Pitufo acude a rescatar a Bebe Pitufo, consigue que la bruja entienda que el leal monstruo del pantano siempre la ha amado.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel y Baltasar se ponen a los mandos de un Robotin gigante para obligar al rey Gerard a que les entregue a Pitufo Robotin. Cuando el Robotin esta a punto de destruir el castillo, Giganton, el nuevo, enorme y extrano amigo de Pitufo Robotin, vence al Robotin. Pitufo Robotin sufre danos durante la batalla, pero Pitufo Carpintero lo arregla y le implanta una caja de voz que le permite decir «¡Hola!».

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La produccion teatral de los Pitufos "Pitufo Robin" se convierte en realidad con un actor real del legendario heroe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos llevan a Abuelo Pitufo al castillo del rey para que pueda conocer a Guillermo. Pero, entre una cosa y otra (sobre todo otra), los Pitufos y Guillermo acaban a bordo de una gran nave vikinga. Los vikingos creen que Guillermo es su mitico gran guerrero, aquel que derrotara al Rey Tormenta. ¿Podran los Pitufos ayudar a Guillermo a salir de este embrollo?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos no quieren ser bucaneros que roban oro de los galeones que pasan cerca de ellos. Sin embargo, caen bajo el hechizo de un amuleto magico y se convierten en la tripulacion del loro Picoazul.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufitos acompanan a Pitufo Lanudo en su mision de esquilar ovejas para obtener lana para la ropa de invierno. Deben superar varios obstaculos, como Gargamel, un lobo y, por ultimo, un pastorcillo que no acepta pitufrutas como pago por la lana. El respeto mutuo entre los Pitufitos y Pitufo Lanudo va creciendo a lo largo del viaje.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos serian un delicioso manjar para el malvado mago Gargamel si no fuera por dos cosas: son dificiles de atrapar y tambien muy pequenos. Ahora bien, si hubiera una formula que permitiera transformar a esos pequenos aperitivos de bocado en grandes y jugosas raciones azules... Gargamel ha tenido una idea...

programme.title: Corazon De Oro
programme.desc: No importa lo que diga Pitufo Filosofo: Pitufo Robotin, la creacion de Pitufo Carpintero, tiene sentimientos como cualquier Pitufo normal. O al menos eso parece... hasta que Pitufo Robotin pierde aquello que Pitufo Carpintero habia colocado en su caja toracica: un corazon de oro. El malvado mago Gargamel y su aprendiz Escrupuloso encuentran al pequeno automata y le colocan un corazon de piedra, lo que augura malos tiempos para los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos En El Laberinto
programme.desc: Pitufo Bromista esta deseando conocer a Melchor el Magnifico, creador del famoso truco maximo de la desaparicion. ¿Conseguira atrapar Gargamel a los Pitufos en el laberinto fantastico de Melchor?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Simon se ha perdido en el bosque buscando a sus padres, una pareja de gigantes. Los Pitufos trataran de llevarlo de vuelta a su casa, pero gargamel aparecera una vez mas con no muy buenas intenciones.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Otra estupenda produccion del teatro de los Pitufos basada en los personajes de Alejandro Dumas. Incluye algunas lineas de Romeo y Julieta. Una obra maestra de la escena.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el Pitufo Filosofo pierde sus gafas deja caer las cosas, tropieza con los objetos, y se convierte en tan patoso como el Pitufo Tontin, que ahora tiene que leer a Filosofo y ayudarle a manejarse. Esta experiencia hace que Filosofo se sienta culpable por la forma en la que siempre se ha burlado de Tontin. Una vez que recibe un nuevo par de gafas, le trata con mas respeto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El futbol (o pitufutbol, como ellos lo llaman) es un pasatiempo que esta bien para un rato. Sin embargo, se vuelve aburrido despues de algunos siglos. Ahora hay un nuevo juego, inventado por uno de los Pitufos: un juego en el que golpeas una bola con un palo y lo tienes que introducir en un agujero de topo...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una aventura dramatica y conmovedora... Pitufina y su mascota Re chillido. La pequena Pitufina esta inundada en lagrimas. ¿Podran los demas pitufos consolarla?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una vez mas, el infalible plan de Gargamel para atrapar a los Pitufos ha fracasado. Los Pitufos aprovechan para gastarle una broma: disfrazados de pequenos angeles azules, le ensenaran a enmendar su conducta...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Creyendo que Bebe Pitufo es un duende, dos cazadores furtivos lo secuestran e intentan que el pequeno les diga donde ha escondido la olla de oro. Papa Pitufo organiza a todos para atacar a los villanos con tartas de pitufrutas y lograr que Bebe Pitufo pueda escapar.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las preocupaciones de Papa Pitufo hacen que le salgan verrugas. La unica forma de librarle de esta enfermedad causada por la indecision es que frote el cuerno de uno de los Verrugosos, los desalinados, viscosos, estupidos y brutales enemigos de las haditas del Bosque de los Sauces...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: A veces ocurren accidentes. ¡En esta ocasion, un error de Pitufo Bromista hace que su sombra cobre vida! Y a la sombra le encanta hacer bromas a todos los habitantes de la Aldea Pitufa...

programme.title: El Cuerno De La Abundancia
programme.desc: Madre Naturaleza siempre da lo mejor de si misma, pero esta vez algo ha salido mal. Su varita no funciona segun lo previsto y dana por accidente la cosecha otonal. Ahora, los Pitufos y todos los animales del bosque se enfrentan a la escasez y el hambre de cara al invierno. El unico lugar donde los Pitufos podrian obtener comida seria la Tierra de la Abundancia. Sin embargo, Gargamel roba el famoso Cuerno de la Abundancia para tender una trampa a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogata consigue los pendientes dorados magicos de Sonoria, que le permitiran oir las voces de los Pitufos desde lejos. Siguiendo los ronquidos de Pitufo Perezoso, esta a punto de llegar hasta la Aldea Pitufa, pero entonces los sonidos del cuerno de Pitufo Armonia comienzan a resonar en sus pendientes y huye enfurecida de vuelta a casa.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo organiza un grupo para navegar a una lejana isla ya que Gargamel ha cortado todos los arboles menos uno para atrapar a los pitufos. Gargamel les sigue pero la Bruja de la isla acaba enviando sus gaviotas tras el.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufina guia a los Pitufos de caminata por la naturaleza, pero Puppy se adelanto demasiado y tras perseguirlo acaban en el territorio de los Wartmongers. El Rey de los Wartmongers acaba haciendoles prisioneros en burbujas, pero un grupo de rebeldes les rescata y consiguen huir a lomos de Puppy.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Natural y Travieso roban la formula de Gargamel para hacer otro Pitufo - otra pitufa para acompanar a Pitufina. Asi pues, crean a Sassette, que crea problemas por doquier. Haciendo uso de su pocion, Papa Pitufo convierte la malvada creacion de Gargamel en una simpatica Sassette.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogapatra, la espantosa, hinchada y vulgar reina del Nilo, no puede dormir y eso hace que le aparezcan grandes ojeras. Su receta para la belleza incluye exprimir a Pitufo Perezoso para extraerle sueno...

programme.title: Secreto Del Pozo De La Aldea
programme.desc: ¿Por que Pitufo Torpe espera dia y noche junto al pozo de la aldea? ¿Cual es el deseo que quiere mantener en secreto? ¿Y como esta involucrado Gargamel en este asunto misterioso? ¿Lograra Gargamel atrapar por fin a los Pitufos?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Creyendo que Bebe Pitufo es un duende, dos cazadores furtivos lo secuestran e intentan que el pequeno les diga donde ha escondido la olla de oro. Papa Pitufo organiza a todos para atacar a los villanos con tartas de pitufrutas y lograr que Bebe Pitufo pueda escapar.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos y Omnibus se hacen amigos de un desdichado joven cuyo maestro le obliga a robar. Pronto, el malvado ladron es entregado al magistrado y el joven esta encantado de irse a vivir con Omnibus.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Tontin, al querer ser el mas popular, roba uno de los hechizos de Gargamel, pero no lo usa bien y acaba convirtiendose en un dragon. Ahora tendran que juntarse todos los Pitufos junto con Papa Pitufo para colarse en el castillo de Gargamel y encontrar el antidoto que hara que Pitufo Tontin vuelva a su forma normal.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El pantano de Greenpeedeepee es el unico lugar donde se pueden encontrar unas algas que son el delicioso e imprescindible ingrediente del famoso estofado de algas de Pitufo Goloso. Desafortunadamente, tambien es un lugar donde te puedes topar con los desagradables Verrugosos. A pesar de que Sasita y los Pitufos le salvan la vida a un joven Verrugoso, acaban siendo apresados por los demas. ¡Pero el Enmascarado Escarlata los salvara! Quiza...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos no quieren ser bucaneros que roban oro de los galeones que pasan cerca de ellos. Sin embargo, caen bajo el hechizo de un amuleto magico y se convierten en la tripulacion del loro Picoazul.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Pitufo Marco Y Los Piratas Pimienta
programme.desc: Los Pitufos navegan para salvar a Marco, que ha sido capturado por el Capitan Pedro Pimienta. Marina y un delfin acaban liberando a Marco.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos se encuentran en una paradisiaca isla del Pacifico. Bueno, no exactamente paradisiaca, ya que hay un volcan muy activo en el que Pitufo Fortachon, tambien muy activo, arriesga tanto su vida como la de Pitufina.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando en la Aldea Pitufa forman una brigada de incendios para combatir las llamas que devoran la cocina de Pitufo Goloso, se dan cuenta de que Gargamel les ha dejado sin agua. Sin embargo, no se da cuenta de la fragilidad de su presa, que se rompe y provoca que el agua arrastre a Gargamel y Azrael e inunde la Aldea Pitufa, extinguiendo el fuego.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Lo que mas le gusta a Sasita es recortar munecas de papel. Lo hace con estilo y entusiasmo. Sin embargo, la formula de revitalizacion de Papa Pitufo salpica por accidente las creaciones recortadas por Sasita con consecuencias imprevistas...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Unos lentes rosados llegan a manos de Pitufina y resultan ser un sucio truco de Gargamel.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo recuerda las emocionantes aventuras de Sonador en el mar, con tortugas, ballenas, islas desiertas...y piratas!

programme.title: NINJA DRAGON - Dragon Ninja
programme.desc: Grandes figuras de la comunidad ninja están siendo asesinadas. Tres ninjas están tratando de descubrir qué personas malvadas quieren poner fin a todos los ninjas, y también rescatar a la hija secuestrada de uno de sus mentores.

programme.title: MYSTERY OF CHESS BOXING-La Leyenda del Gran Luchador
programme.desc: Supuestamente muerto, ex oficial amargado, The Ghost Face Killer ha regresado y buscando venganza contra los maestros de artes marciales que una vez se le opusieron: su nombre es infame y su estilo de lucha de los Cinco Elementos es mortal. Mientras tanto, el joven Ah Pao se une a una escuela de artes marciales para convertirse en un gran luchador para vengarse del hombre que mató a su padre. Se vuelve muy bueno rápidamente, pero el tiempo lo es todo y su llegada a la escuela en relación con el regreso del Asesino de la Cara Fantasma lo ve sospechoso de estar conectado y, por lo tanto, expulsado de la escuela. Cae bajo la tutela de un anciano maestro de ajedrez en la ciudad mientras todo el tiempo el foco de su venganza mata su camino cada vez más cerca
